article.description: — Braden Norris and Philip Alston both scored 10 points as Loyola Chicago beat George Mason 80-59 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Norris and Alston have 10 apiece as Loyola Chicago takes down George Mason 80-59
article.linkText: Norris and Alston have 10 apiece as Loyola Chicago takes down George Mason 80-59
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Braden Norris and Philip Alston both scored 10 points as Loyola Chicago beat George Mason 80-59 on Saturday night. Norris added eight assists and four steals for the Ramblers (20-7, 12-2 Atlantic 10 Conference). Alston finished 4 of 6 from the field. Dame Adelekun had nine points and was 3 of 4 shooting and 3 of 5 from the free throw line. The Ramblers prolonged their winning streak to seven games. The Patriots (18-9, 7-7) were led in scoring by Amari Kelly, who finished with 19 points. Darius Maddox added 17 points for George Mason. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
